        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 7:10PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 710 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles west of Conlen, or 13 miles north of Dalhart, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Conlen and Dalhart.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
